c.): haryata, V, 54, 15.--prati haryate, it is\nacceptable, V, 57, 1; prati haryanti, they yearn for me, I, 165, 4.\n\nharyata, delicious: ([147](sbe3222.htm#page_147) seq.)\n\nhava, call: havam, I, 86, 2; V, 87, 8; 9; VIII, 7, 9; I, 114, 11; I, 2, 1.\n\nhavana, invocation: havanani, V, 56, 2.\n\nhavana- _s_ rut, mindful of invocations: havana- _s_ rut, II, 33, 15:2\n\nhavas, call, prayer: havasa, I, 64, 12:1; VI, 66, 11.\n\nhavi _h_ -k _r i_t, sacrificer: havi _h_ -k _r i_tam, I, 166, 2.\n\nhavishmat, carrying ablations: havishman, I, 167, 6; havishmanta _h_ , X, 77,\n1; I, 114, 8.\n\nhavis, sacrifice: havi _h_ , VII, 59, 9; 1, 114, 3; havisha, X, 121, 1 to 9;\nI, 166, 3; X, 168, 4; havisha _h_ , V, 60, 6; havi\xc2\xb4 _m_ shi, I, 170, 5; VII,\n57, 6; havi _h_ -bhi _h_ , II, 33, 5.\n\nhaviman, invocation: haviman, VII, 56, 15; havima-bhi _h_ , II, 33, 5.\n\nhavya, called to assist: havya _h_ , VIII, 20, 20:1.\n\nhavya, offering, libation: havya\xc2\xb4, I, 171, 4; VII, 56, 12; 59, 5; VIII, 20, 9;\n10; 16.\n\nhavya-dati, offering: havya-datim, V, 55, 10.\n\nhas, to laugh: _g_ aksh from has, ([284](sbe3229.htm#page_284).)\n\nhasta, hand: hasta _h_ (bhesha _g_ a _h_ _g_ alasha _h_ ), II, 33, 71; haste\nbibhrat bhesha _g_ a\xc2\xb4, I, 114, 5; hastayo _h_ , I, 38, 1; hasteshu, I, 37, 3;\n168, 3.\n\nhastin, elephant: hastina _h_ , I, 64, 7:2.\n\nha, to flee: _g_ ihita, I, 37, 7:1; dyau _h_ _g_ ihite b _ri_ hat, the sky\nmakes wide room, VIII, 20, 6.--apa ahasata, ut ahasata, (VIII, 7, 2:1.)--ni\n_g_ ihate, they bend down, V, 57, 3; 60, 2; VIII, 7, 34; ni ahasata, they have\ngone down, VIII, 7, 2:1.--pra _g_ ihite, flies out of your way, I, 166, 5:2.\n\nha, to forsake, to leave behind: a _g_ ahatana, VIII, 7, 31; hitva\xc2\xb4, V, 53,\n14.\n\nharidra, yellow: ([232](sbe3227.htm#page_232).)\n\nhi, indeed, truly, for \xe2\x80\xa6: _k_ it hi, VII, 59, 7; hi kam, VII, 59, 5; vidma hi,\nI, 170, 3; VIII, 20, 3.\n\nhi, to prepare: hinomi, VII, 56, 12.\n\nhi _m_ s, to hurt: ma\xc2\xb4 na _h_ hi _m_ sit, X, 121, 9.\n\nhita, friend: hita\xc2\xb4 _h_ -iva, I, 166, 3; hita, kind, = su-dhita,\n([225](sbe3227.htm#page_225).)\n\nhinv, to rouse: hinvantu, II, 34, 12.\n\nhimavat, the snowy mountain: himavanta _h_ , X, 121, 4; (p.\n[4](sbe3215.htm#page_4).)\n\nhima, winter: _s_ atam hima _h_ , during a hundred\n\np. 529\n\nwinters, I, 64, 14; V, 54, 15; II, 33, 2.\n\nhira _n_ ya, gold: hira _n_ yam-iva, I, 43, 5; hira _n_ yai _h_ , with golden\nornaments, V, 60, 4; 11, 33, 9.\n\nHira _n_ ya-garbha, the Golden Child: hira _n_ ya-garbha _h_ , X, 121, 1:1;\n(p. [3](sbe3215.htm#page_3) seq.; [6](sbe3215.htm#page_6).)\n\nhira _n_ ya- _k_ akra, on golden wheels: hira _n_ ya- _k_ akran, I, 88, 5.\n\nhira _n_ ya-nirni _g_ , gold-adorned: hira _n_ ya-nirnik, I, 167, 3.\n\nhira _n_ ya-pa _n_ i, golden-hoofed: hira _n_ yapa _n_ i-bhi _h_ , VIII, 7,\n27; (I, 38, 11:1.)\n\nhira _n_ yaya, golden: hira _n_ yayebhi _h_ , I, 64, 11; hira _n_ yayam (va\n_g_ ram), I, 85, 9; hira _n_ yayi _h_ , V, 54, 11; VIII, 7, 25; hira _n_ yayan\n(atkan), V, 55, 6; hira _n_ yaya _h_ , golden-coloured, V, 87, 5; hira _n_\nyayasa _h_ , golden (chariots), VI, 66, 2:1; hira _n_ yaye ko _s_ e, VIII, 20,\n8:1.\n\nhira _n_ ya-ratha, on golden chariots: hira _n_ ya-ratha _h_ , V, 57, 1.\n\nhira _n_ ya-var _n_ a, golden-coloured: hira _n_ ya-var _n_ an, II, 34, 11.\n\nhira _n_ ya-va _s_ i, armed with golden daggers: hira _n_ ya-va _s_ ibhi _h_ ,\nVIII, 7, 32.\n\nhira _n_ ya- _s_ ipra, golden-jawed: hira _n_ ya- _s_ ipra _h_ , II, 34, 3:3.\n\nhiri- _s_ ipra, golden-jawed (or -helmeted): (II, 34, 3:3.)\n\nhi _d_ , to hate: _g_ ihi _li_ re, VII, 58, 5; hi _l_ itasya, furious, VII,\n46, 4.\n\nhu, to sacrifice: _g_ uhuma _h_ (c. Gen.), X, 121, 10; _g_ uhavama te havi _h_\n, I, 114, 3.\n\nh _ri_ , to be angry: yatha na h _ri_ _n_ ishe, II, 33, 15.\n\nh _r i_ _d_ , heart: h _ri_ da\xc2\xb4, I, 171, 2; V, 56, 2; vasyasa h _ri_ da\xc2\xb4,\nVIII, 20, 18; h _ri_ de, 1, 43, 1; X, 186, 1; h _ri_ t-su, I, 168, 3.\n\nhe _l_ as, anger: he _l_ a _h_ , I, 171, 1; 114, 4.\n\nheti, weapon: heti _h_ , II, 33, 14; hetaya _h_ , pp. xlviii;\n[l](sbe3205.htm#page_l).\n\nhot _ri_ , caller: hot _ri_ shu, VIII, 20, 20:1.\n\nhot _ri_ , the Hot _ri_ priest: hota, VII, 56, 18; VIII, 94, 6:1; pa _\xc3\xb1_ _k_ a\nhot _r i_n, II, 34, 14; hot _ri_ shu, (VIII, 20, 20:1.)\n\nhraduni-v _r i_t, whirling the hail: hraduni-v _r i_ta _h_ , V, 54, 3.\n\nhru, to injure: vi hru _n_ ati, he can injure, I, 166, 12; (I, 166, 8:1.)\n\nhv _ri_ , or hvar, to overthrow: _g_ uhuranta, I, 43, 8; hru and hvar, (I,\n166, 8:1.)\n\nhve, to call, to invoke: havamahe, II, 34, 11; VIII, 7, 6; 11; I, 114, 8;\nhvaye, V, 56, 5; huve, VIII, 94, 10 to 12; I, 2, 7; havate, VII, 56, 18;\nhavate, he is invoked (?), II, 33, 5:1; vipram havamanam, VIII, 7, 30.--anu\nhvaya, call after, V, 53, 1 6.--ava hvaye, I call down, V, 56, 1.--a\xc2\xb4\nhuvamahe, we call towards us, V, 56, 8; a\xc2\xb4 huve, V, 56, 9; VII, 56, 10; a\xc2\xb4 _g_\nohaviti, he calls again and again, VII, 56, 18.--ni hvayamahe, we call down,\nI, 114, 4; 5.--pra huyase, thou art called forth, I, 19, 1.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: II. List of Important Passages](sbe3295.htm)\n\n'